id: pm-vhdc
title: Validate UUID fields at telemetry ingestion boundary
description: Remote telemetry worker logs repeatedly show worker_insert_failed invalid input syntax for type uuid when events contain non-UUID installation_id/session_id/event_id values. Invalid payloads should be rejected (or sanitized/quarantined) before queue insert to prevent retry churn and queue pollution.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: observability,pm-cli,telemetry,validation
created_at: "2026-04-26T08:38:49.149Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-03T13:54:31.143Z"
author: codex-agent
estimated_minutes: 180
acceptance_criteria: Ingestion path validates UUID-typed identifiers before queueing; invalid payloads are dropped/quarantined with explicit counters and do not repeatedly fail worker inserts.
parent: pm-lnq3
resolution: "Telemetry API now rejects invalid UUID payloads with explicit counters, and the worker drops legacy malformed UUID events without requeue churn."
expected_result: Invalid UUID telemetry payloads are rejected at ingestion and do not create persistent queue or worker insert failures.
actual_result: Invalid UUID payloads now return 400 with field-level detail; rejected UUID counters increment; worker drained poison backlog and queue remains at 0/0 without recurring UUID insert-failed loops.
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-lnq3,parent,"2026-04-26T08:38:49.149Z",codex-agent,null
comments[11]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-26T08:38:49.149Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence: pm context --limit 10; pm search 'telemetry worker invalid uuid' --limit 10; pm list-open --limit 20; pm list-in-progress --limit 20. Net-new because current telemetry open items cover docs/health visibility but not ingestion boundary UUID validation and worker retry churn."
  "2026-04-26T08:42:50.281Z",codex-agent,"Remote verification evidence 2026-04-26: docker compose services healthy on [redacted_user]@[redacted_host] (telemetry-api/worker/rabbitmq/postgres/prometheus/loki/tempo/alloy/grafana); /healthz returned ok queue pm.telemetry.events; synthetic POST /v1/events accepted=1; Postgres telemetry_events count increased (9516->9519) and live command ingest confirmed (stats delta +1); DSAR export/delete scripts executed successfully for probe installation UUID. Outstanding failure signal: telemetry-worker logs repeated worker_insert_failed invalid UUID errors for non-UUID identifiers, indicating ingestion boundary lacks strict UUID validation before worker insert."
  "2026-04-26T09:56:01.971Z",codex-agent,"Remote telemetry verification 2026-04-26: all stack services are running and healthy, public /healthz and Grafana API health respond (200), and a UUID-based synthetic event command=remote-audit-smoke was accepted and persisted in Postgres. RabbitMQ queue depth remains non-zero (messages=4, messages_unacknowledged=4) while telemetry-worker logs repeatedly show worker_insert_failed invalid UUID errors for non-UUID identifiers, confirming poison-message churn when ingestion accepts malformed UUID fields."
  "2026-04-26T13:16:13.950Z",cursor-agent,"Fresh remote audit evidence 2026-04-26: UUID synthetic event 42fc2624-e0a9-409b-ba25-42f380274a79 was accepted by /v1/events and persisted in Postgres, but RabbitMQ still reported messages=4 then Prometheus showed rabbitmq_queue_messages=3 and rabbitmq_queue_messages_unacked=3 while worker logs repeated worker_insert_failed invalid UUID errors for non-UUID payloads. This confirms valid events flow while poison messages continue to churn."
  "2026-04-27T19:27:42.459Z",codex-agent,"Wave kickoff 2026-04-27: baseline captured via pm context/list-open telemetry snapshot; item claimed and moved to in_progress. Execution path will run remote diagnostics on [redacted_user]@[redacted_host] stack, implement UUID boundary validation in telemetry-api/worker pipeline, and verify no recurring worker_insert_failed invalid UUID churn. Evidence logs linked under scripts/prod/telemetry baseline and pm-vhdc execution log."
  "2026-04-27T19:29:19.551Z",codex-agent,"Remote baseline 2026-04-27: stack health checks passed (telemetry-api healthz ok true queue pm.telemetry.events; Grafana API health database ok). RabbitMQ queue baseline was messages=5/unacked=5 and increased to 6/6 after posting a synthetic invalid UUID telemetry event. Ingestion endpoint still accepted malformed IDs (response ok accepted=1), while telemetry-worker logs continue repeated worker_insert_failed invalid uuid errors. Detailed evidence captured in scripts/prod/telemetry/2026-04-27-backlog-wave-baseline.md and scripts/prod/telemetry/2026-04-27-pm-vhdc-execution-log.md."
  "2026-04-27T19:36:03.760Z",codex-agent,"Implementation 2026-04-27: patched remote telemetry-api/app.py to validate and normalize UUID fields before queue publish (event_id, installation_id, optional session_id) and added pm_telemetry_rejected_uuid_events_total field-scoped counter. Patched telemetry-api/worker.py to drop malformed UUID events with ack and explicit worker_drop_invalid_uuid_fields totals instead of nacking/requeueing. Rebuilt telemetry-api/worker images and restarted both services."
  "2026-04-27T19:36:07.070Z",codex-agent,"Verification 2026-04-27 after rollout: queue drained to messages=0/unacked=0, worker logs showed poison backlog drain via worker_drop_invalid_uuid_fields total=6 with no recurring worker_insert_failed UUID churn, invalid UUID POST now returns 400, valid UUID POST returns 200 accepted=1, and /metrics exposes pm_telemetry_rejected_uuid_events_total labels for event_id/installation_id/session_id."
  "2026-04-27T19:44:37.688Z",codex-agent,"Final evidence 2026-04-27: remote smoke checks show telemetry-api healthz ok and queue pm.telemetry.events at 0/0; worker churn no longer loops with worker_insert_failed UUID failures after boundary hardening rollout."
  "2026-05-01T19:29:31.935Z",cursor-agent,"History drift audit: hash mismatch is from pre-history-tracking era edits. Accepted as historical legacy drift."
  "2026-05-03T12:11:42.443Z",audit-agent,"author=audit-agent,created_at=now,text=SECURITY REDACTION: Prior linked files and tests reference remote host paths for UUID validation fix. These are internal infrastructure references and do not expose credentials."
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-27T19:29:23.382Z",codex-agent,"Current failure mode is queue poison churn: invalid UUID payloads are accepted at ingress and repeatedly fail at worker insert, causing perpetual backlog growth and noisy worker logs."
  "2026-04-27T19:36:10.924Z",codex-agent,"Dual boundary hardening is now in place: ingress rejects malformed UUID payloads for new events, while worker ack-drop logic clears any legacy poison messages already in RabbitMQ without requeue loops."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-27T19:36:14.819Z",codex-agent,"When a queue already contains poison telemetry events, API-only validation is insufficient; adding worker-side ack-drop validation prevents indefinite nack/requeue churn and restores queue drain deterministically."
